It’s understood a community member made the discovery in the Bankhara village earlier this week. JOHANNESBURG - Bodies of two young girls have been found in a chest freezer in a village just outside Kuruman. It’s understood a community member made the discovery in the Bankhara village earlier this week. The circumstances around their deaths have not yet been disclosed. Police spokesperson Mohale Ramatseba said: “At this stage, the investigations have not yet been concluded. Our suspicion is that the children might have been playing and might have locked themselves into a freezer.”